</taxonomicName>
with its nonstriate elytra is easily differentiated from all other Indian 
<taxonomicName id="E6BC4D040B42D21AFD422668234517E2" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1876" box="[760,889,379,401]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Styphlomerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13C8EA950B42D21AFD422668234517E2" box="[760,889,379,401]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="470">Styphlomerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all of which have striate elytra.
</paragraph>
